OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 20 Jun to Mon 29 Jun
OL,6,FThere is the possibility of some very
OL,7,Fwarm and humid weather across parts of
OL,8,Fsouth and southeast Britain at the
OL,9,Fstart of this period and perhaps the
OL,10,Fchance of a few thunderstorms too.
OL,11,FGenerally more changeable to the north
OL,12,Fand west at first, but there is a
OL,13,Fsignal for high pressure to build more
OL,14,Fwidely as we move towards the latter
OL,15,Fpart of June. This likely brings more
OL,16,Fwidely drier, settled conditions with
OL,17,Ftemperatures probably remaining above
OL,18,Faverage for most. It is still possible
OL,19,Fthat Atlantic low pressure may still
OL,20,Fbring brief spells of wet and windy
OL,21,Fweather. There is a chance that the
OL,22,Fhot conditions, could return
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fnorthwards accompanied by a
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fthunderstorm risk; this all dependent
OL,25,Fon the orientation of the
OL,26,Faforementioned high pressure.
